                  "display": "Summarization of encounter note"
                }
              ]
            },
            "title": "Synthesis"
          },
          {
            "text": {
              "status": "generated",
              "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">Dear colleague, I am writing to inform you regarding the discharge of your 61-year-old male patient, admitted on 27.03.2021 due to substance dependence disorder. Upon admission, comprehensive psychiatric and somatic assessment was performed, including structured addiction history, laboratory screening, and urine toxicology. The patient presented with polysubstance dependence, primarily alcohol and benzodiazepines, with signs of early withdrawal. Vital monitoring was initiated immediately. Treatment included medically supervised detoxification with benzodiazepine tapering protocol, vitamin supplementation (thiamine), and supportive psychiatric counselling. Withdrawal symptoms were managed successfully without severe complications. The patient participated in motivational interviewing sessions and psychoeducation regarding addiction. At discharge on 03.04.2021, the patient was stabilised, cooperative, and motivated for outpatient follow-up. Referral to an outpatient addiction therapy programme has been arranged. We kindly ask for continued monitoring and support in your practice.</div>"
            },
